---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-uk-expats-need', text: 'What UK Expats Need', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'uk-coverage-options', text: 'UK Coverage Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'special-considerations', text: 'Special Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
  { title: 'Worldwide Insurance', href: '/best/worldwide-insurance' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Long-Term Insurance', href: '/best/long-term-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'ukNetwork', header: 'UK Network' },
  { key: 'ukOption', header: 'UK Coverage' },
  { key: 'europeCoverage', header: 'Europe Coverage' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', ukNetwork: 'Excellent', ukOption: 'Optional', europeCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'UK returnees' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', ukNetwork: 'Very Good', ukOption: 'Optional', europeCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'Global + UK' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', ukNetwork: 'Good', ukOption: 'Optional', europeCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'Europe-based' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', ukNetwork: 'Good', ukOption: 'Optional', europeCoverage: 'Good', bestFor: 'Global coverage' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', ukNetwork: 'Very Good', ukOption: 'Optional', europeCoverage: 'Excellent', bestFor: 'European expats' },
];

const considerationsColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'importance', header: 'Why It Matters' },
  { key: 'recommendation', header: 'Recommendation' },
];

const considerationsRows = [
  { factor: 'NHS access', importance: 'May lose NHS eligibility abroad', recommendation: 'Verify NHS status' },
  { factor: 'UK return visits', importance: 'Family visits, potential return', recommendation: 'Include UK option' },
  { factor: 'European coverage', importance: 'Post-Brexit EHIC changes', recommendation: 'Ensure Europe included' },
  { factor: 'Private UK care', importance: 'Avoid NHS waits if returning', recommendation: 'Consider UK private network' },
  { factor: 'Pension/tax', importance: 'UK tax residency implications', recommendation: 'Consult advisor' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Insurance for UK Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for British expats. Find plans with UK coverage options, strong European networks, and benefits designed for UK citizens living abroad."
  headline="Best Insurance for UK Expats"
  subheadline="British expats have unique needs—NHS considerations, UK return coverage, and post-Brexit European healthcare. Here are the best insurance options for UK citizens abroad."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-uk-expat-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for UK Expats</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best options for British citizens abroad:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇬🇧</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for UK Expats</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">UK-based insurer with excellent UK private network, familiar British service, and strong global coverage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🌐</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Global + UK</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Excellent worldwide coverage with good UK options and European network.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇪🇺</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Europe</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Excellent European coverage for UK expats living in EU countries post-Brexit.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💡</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Key Consideration</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">NHS Access Changes</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Living abroad affects NHS eligibility. Private international insurance fills the gap.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-uk-expats-need">What UK Expats Need</h2>
  <p>
    British citizens living abroad have specific insurance considerations:
  </p>

  <h3>NHS Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>NHS access depends on residency status</li>
    <li>Living abroad may end NHS eligibility</li>
    <li>Return visits may face charges</li>
    <li>Private insurance covers UK gaps</li>
    <li>International insurance essential abroad</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Post-Brexit European Healthcare</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>EHIC replaced by GHIC with limitations</li>
    <li>S1 forms for some retirees in EU</li>
    <li>Private insurance recommended for EU living</li>
    <li>Reciprocal agreements vary by country</li>
    <li>Don't rely solely on state agreements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>UK Return Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Family visits to UK</li>
    <li>Access to UK specialists</li>
    <li>Avoid NHS waiting lists</li>
    <li>Potential permanent return</li>
    <li>UK private hospital network</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Coverage for British Expats"
    description="Compare plans with UK and global coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">UK Expat Plan Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best for UK Expats</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global is the natural choice for British expats.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>UK-headquartered, understands UK expats</li>
    <li>Excellent UK private hospital network</li>
    <li>British service style and expectations</li>
    <li>Strong European coverage</li>
    <li>Global network worldwide</li>
    <li>UK customer service team</li>
    <li>Familiar claims processes</li>
    <li>Premium coverage quality</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing reflects premium service. Best for those wanting UK-style coverage worldwide. Excellent for UK returnees.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best Global + UK</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers excellent worldwide coverage with UK options.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>World-class global coverage</li>
    <li>Good UK coverage options</li>
    <li>Strong European network</li>
    <li>Modular flexibility</li>
    <li>1.5M+ providers globally</li>
    <li>Competitive pricing</li>
    <li>24/7 global support</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> UK adds to premium. Good balance of global and UK coverage. Excellent flexibility.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Allianz Care — Best for Europe</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care excels for UK expats in Europe.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Excellent European coverage</li>
    <li>Good UK options</li>
    <li>Strong EU network</li>
    <li>Multilingual support</li>
    <li>Competitive European pricing</li>
    <li>Good for EU residents</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Best for Europe-focused coverage. Good UK options but not as strong as Bupa. Excellent for EU living.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our full Allianz Care review</a></p>

  <h2 id="uk-coverage-options">UK Coverage Options</h2>

  <h3>Full UK Inclusion</h3>
  <p>
    Complete UK coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>UK private healthcare fully covered</li>
    <li>Direct billing at UK hospitals</li>
    <li>No NHS reliance needed</li>
    <li>Access to UK specialists</li>
    <li>Adds to premium cost</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>UK for Treatment Only</h3>
  <p>
    Limited UK coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage when referred to UK</li>
    <li>Not for routine UK visits</li>
    <li>For specialist UK treatment</li>
    <li>Lower premium impact</li>
    <li>Check specific terms</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Emergency UK Only</h3>
  <p>
    Basic UK protection:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Emergency care in UK covered</li>
    <li>Routine UK care excluded</li>
    <li>Good for occasional visitors</li>
    <li>Lowest UK premium impact</li>
    <li>NHS may cover some care anyway</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Your UK Healthcare Connection"
    description="Find the right level of UK coverage."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="special-considerations">Special Considerations for UK Expats</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={considerationsColumns} rows={considerationsRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>NHS Eligibility</h3>
  <p>
    Understanding NHS rules:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>NHS based on "ordinary residence" in UK</li>
    <li>Living abroad may end eligibility</li>
    <li>Short visits may still qualify for some care</li>
    <li>Charges for overseas visitors increasing</li>
    <li>Private insurance provides certainty</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Post-Brexit EU Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Changes for UK citizens in EU:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>GHIC for short trips (replaces EHIC)</li>
    <li>S1 form for some retirees in EU</li>
    <li>Varies by individual EU country</li>
    <li>Private insurance recommended regardless</li>
    <li>Don't assume reciprocal coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>UK State Pension Considerations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Can receive UK pension abroad</li>
    <li>Some countries freeze pension increases</li>
    <li>Tax implications vary by country</li>
    <li>Doesn't affect insurance options</li>
    <li>Plan finances including insurance premiums</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Returning to the UK</h3>
  <p>
    Planning potential return:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>NHS eligibility may have waiting period</li>
    <li>Private insurance bridges the gap</li>
    <li>Keep UK coverage option for smooth return</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions handled better</li>
    <li>Plan ahead for transition</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I lose NHS access when I move abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally yes, after a period. NHS eligibility is based on ordinary residence in the UK. Once you're no longer ordinarily resident, you may face charges for NHS services. Rules vary by circumstances.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I still use the NHS when visiting the UK?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on circumstances. Short visits may qualify for some NHS care. Extended visitors may face charges. Emergency care is provided regardless but may be charged. Private insurance provides certainty.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need insurance if I have GHIC/S1?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, private insurance is recommended. GHIC covers emergency and necessary care but not everything. S1 forms have specific conditions. Private insurance provides comprehensive coverage and choice.
  </p>

  <h3>Which insurer is best for UK expats?</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global is the natural choice for most UK expats—UK-headquartered, excellent UK private network, and British service style. Cigna Global is also excellent for more global coverage with UK options.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I include UK in my coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes. Most UK expats visit family, may need UK specialists, or might return permanently. UK coverage provides peace of mind and avoids NHS uncertainties. Consider your specific circumstances.
  </p>

  <h3>What about European coverage post-Brexit?</h3>
  <p>
    Essential if living in EU. Brexit changed healthcare arrangements. While some reciprocal agreements exist, private international insurance is the safest option for comprehensive coverage in EU countries.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. NHS rules and Brexit arrangements evolve. We are not insurance brokers or legal advisors. Verify current rules and coverage directly.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
